{"generation_id":"gen_base_aflily_e294ad14","status":"IN_QUEUE","input_text":"The air in the small room carried the faint, rhythmic hum of the computer, a soft warmth emanating from its bulky frame. Dust motes danced in the light filtering through the unseen window, settling on the worn wooden shelves and the tangle of wires behind the monitor. On the screen, a vibrant world of pixels glowed, a colorful game paused mid-action, a testament to a hard-won moment.\n\nTwo young faces, bright with exhilaration, framed the scene. Their mouths were wide open in shouts of triumph, eyes shining with a shared victory only they understood. Both boys had their thumbs thrust upwards, a universal sign of \"we did it!\" Their arms stretched out, almost embracing the old monitor, a silent cheer passing between them. It was a bubble of pure, unadulterated friendship, the kind where a simple game sparked such explosive joy.\n\nThey were in sync, two halves of a perfectly understood moment. I hold this laughter, this feeling of pure connection when the world beyond these walls faded away. They didn't know then how life would shift, how paths might diverge. But this snapshot, this burst of shared triumph, would always be a warm reminder of a bond that felt invincible, a small victory echoing through time.","voice_id":"af_lily","voice_name":"Lily","model":"base","tokens":306,"dollar_cost":0.00306,"method":null,"audio_url":null,"error_message":null,"created_at":"2026-03-16T08:08:06.082902","started_at":null,"completed_at":null}